Spring Tutorial 11: Bean Scope
====================================================================================================
Basic Bean Scope
1. Singleton
2. Prototype

---
default bean scope is singleton
But if we want prototype, then
<bean id="triangle" class="me.tomato.Triangle" autowire="byName" scope="prototype">
---


Web-aware Context Bean Scope
1. Request: new bean for new request
2. Session: new bean for new session
3. Global Session: new bean for a HTTP request
